        "q": "Summarize the book of Genesis: author, date, theme, and outline.",
        "a": "**Author & date.** Moses; c. 1446–1406 B.C. (the wilderness period).\n\n**Genre.** Narrative / Law (Torah).\n\n**Theme.** Beginnings: God creates a good world, humanity falls into sin, and God answers that ruin by launching redemption through a covenant with Abraham's family.\n\n**Outline.**\n- 1–11 — Primeval history: creation, fall, flood, Babel\n- 12–25 — Abraham: the call and covenant promises\n- 25–28 — Isaac and the passing of the promise\n- 28–36 — Jacob and the twelve tribes\n- 37–50 — Joseph and the descent into Egypt\n\n**Christ & significance.** The first promise of the gospel (3:15) and the Abrahamic covenant (12:1–3) chart the trajectory of redemptive history that is fulfilled in Christ, the promised seed in whom all nations are blessed.",
